olive oil
1 clove garlic
1 stalk celery
2 radish
1 carrot
1 tin sweetcorn
½ lemon
1 packet ginger paste
1 tbs sesame oil
½ tbs soy sauce
½ tsp brown sugar
1 sachet Sweet Soy Seasoning
1 packet beef strips
1 bag super slaw
1 packet garlic aioli
1 packet Roasted Peanuts & Cashew Mix

• Finely chop garlic. Thinly slice celery and radish. Grate the carrot. Drain the sweetcorn.
• Zest lemon to get a pinch, then slice into wedges.
• Add ginger paste and garlic to a large heatproof bowl.

• In a large frying pan, heat the sesame oil over high heat until just smoking, 30 seconds, then carefully pour the sesame oil over the garlic-ginger mixture.
• Add the soy sauce, brown sugar and a generous squeeze of lemon juice. Stir well to combine. Set aside.

TIP: The hot oil will bubble up and 'cook' the ginger and garlic.

• In a medium bowl, combine sweet soy seasoning, lemon zest and a drizzle of olive oil. Add beef strips and toss to coat.
• Return the frying pan to high heat with a drizzle of olive oil. When oil is hot, cook beef strips and corn in batches, until browned and cooked through,
1-2 minutes. Transfer to a plate and set aside.

TIP: Cooking the meat in batches over high heat helps it stay tender.

• Add super slaw to the dressing, along with celery, radish, carrot and garlic aioli. Toss to combine and season to taste.
• Divide ginger slaw between bowls. Top with beef and corn.
• Garnish with roasted peanut & cashew mix. Serve with any remaining lemon wedges. Enjoy!